<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-16T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-16T17:00:00-05:00" n="97" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/457a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-16T18:00:00-04:00">August 16,
                                    1935—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>215. All the important news associations have reports from London that
                            British Government has extended invitations to Washington Treaty powers
                            for informal conference, London, about October. In reply to inquiries at
                            press conference today I have stated no such invitation has been
                            received.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>